fruit.name: Gum-Gum Fruit
fruit.description: Gomu Gomu no Mi, also known as the Fruit of Gum-Gum in French, is a Paramecia-type Demon Fruit that imparts the same properties as rubber to its user's body, making the eater an Elastic Man (ゴム人間, Gomu Ningen). This was once a treasure that Shanks and his crew had taken from a World Government convoy, protected by CP9, but which was accidentally eaten by Monkey D. Luffy

fruit.name: Fruit of the Human
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-human. As the user was originally a reindeer, he acquired an intelligence that enabled him to acquire a vast amount of knowledge. Before the ellipse, Chopper had to take a Rumble-Ball to get more transformations for 3 minutes1 (if after 3 minutes he took another Rumble-Ball, he no longer controlled his transformations, and if he took a 3rd Rumble-Ball, he became a gigantic but unconscious monster, destroying enemies and allies alike). After the ellipse, he masters all transformations perfectly, and when he takes a Rumble-Ball he becomes the gigantic monster, but in control of himself.

fruit.name: Fruit Des Éclosions
fruit.description: Allows the user to grow body parts (or even clones) anywhere, even on another person. He can assemble several copies of the same limb to create, for example, giant hands, or create clones of himself to deceive opponents.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Resurrection
fruit.description: Allows the owner to come back to life after death (this power only works once). Its possessor can take his soul out of his body, take it through walls and return it to his body as he wishes. Similarly, if his head is cut off, his fruit enables him to bring it back to his shoulders by sheer force of will (the soul is still connected to his body). If his power is combined with a sword, he can freeze any enemy he touches, thanks to the icy cold of the depths that his soul brings to his sword.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Barrier
fruit.description: Enables its user to generate almost invisible barriers to deflect or block any attack. These barriers can take on a wide range of shapes (racket, stairs, etc.).

fruit.name: Armo-Fruit
fruit.description: Enables the user to transform body parts into weapons of all kinds (revolver, cannon, saber, missile...).

fruit.name: Fruit de la Couture
fruit.description: Allows the user to sew and unstitch anything on flat surfaces. These seams are strong enough to hold people 'hooked' to the floor.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Insect, Scarab-Rhinoceros version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can transform into a rhinoceros beetle. It enables the user to fly.
fruit.roman_name: Mushi Mushi no Mi, Moderu Kabutomushi

fruit.name: Fruit of the Insect, Wasp version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a wasp. It enables the user to fly.
fruit.roman_name: Mushi Mushi no Mi, Moderu Suzumebachi

fruit.name: Fruit of Fragmentation
fruit.description: Allows you to separate your body into several parts and levitate them. The parts can fly in an area 200 meters in diameter around the feet. The feet, on the other hand, cannot levitate (although they can walk). This power makes the user immune to sharp weapons. Any part of the user will nevertheless remain sensitive to the pain felt by other detached body parts.

fruit.name: Fruit Glisse-Glisse
fruit.description: Smoothes the user's skin, making it more beautiful. What's more, the skin becomes ultra-slick, deflecting objects touching the body.

fruit.name: Ciro-Fruit
fruit.description: Produces a fast-hardening wax that can be molded into any shape. This wax becomes very resistant when hardened, but remains just as vulnerable to heat as normal wax. Note that it can block most poisons.

fruit.name: Ramollo fruit
fruit.description: Emits a ray that slows down the movement of any mass for 30 seconds. This ray can be reflected by a mirror, and the user is not immune to its effects.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Shadow
fruit.description: Allows its user to control shadows. He can cut the shadows of anyone with a pair of scissors, and the shadows thus removed can be locked into inert bodies, giving rise to zombies possessing the combat techniques of the person to whom the shadow belonged. If shadows are enclosed in the body of a living being, they can only remain for a short time, depending on the latter's mental strength. For example, its user has consumed up to 1000 of them. It should also be noted that the user can use his own shadow and make it tangible. He can therefore use his shadow to teleport or protect himself from physical attacks.

fruit.name: Fruit of Invisibility
fruit.description: Enables the user to make himself and everything he touches (living beings, firearms, etc.) invisible.

fruit.name: Fruit of Ectoplasm
fruit.description: Allows its user to create ghosts with various abilities, such as undermining morale or exploding. It also allows its user to make himself intangible: the user can float in the air and pass through walls, but has the great disadvantage of leaving his inert body defenseless.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Scalpel
fruit.description: This fruit allows the eater to create a sphere in which he can do anything from interchanging one thing with another to extending the range of his sword strokes. It can also cut up its victims without killing them, or cancel the gravity of anything in the sphere. Its user can even remove a person's heart while leaving them alive, or swap the personalities of several people. This fruit is considered the "ultimate demon fruit" because of its unique ability to grant another person eternal youth in exchange for the user's life.

fruit.name: Magnéto-Fruit
fruit.description: Allows the user to manipulate magnetic forces, attracting metals to him or her but also repelling them. It can also create a metal golem when a large quantity is gathered.

fruit.name: Fruit du Château
fruit.description: Allows the user to become a man-castle, with the following special features: anyone within a certain range of him (marked by a red zone) is miniaturized, and anyone who comes out is restored to normal size; the holder can create loopholes in his body to enable the besieged to "defend the fortress". The user's interior is made up of different rooms where members can live. The user can also miniaturize himself to join his guests, but leaves his physical body inert. He can replace his legs with a system of caterpillar tracks to move around more easily, or transform himself into a sort of armed, fortified golem that can serve as a refuge for his allies.

crew.name: The crew of Les Moines Dépravés

fruit.name: Passion fruit
fruit.description: Allows its possessor to use love as a lethal weapon through a variety of means. These techniques are designed to petrify people or objects, and are all heart-shaped (rays, piercing kisses, kicks, etc.). This power only works on people with an attraction (however slight) for the user. When the user reverses the process, the victim has no memory of the time spent petrified.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Reptile, Anaconda version
fruit.description: allows its user to transform himself into an anaconda as he pleases: the user can turn his hair into steel-hard snakes.
fruit.roman_name: Hebi Hebi no Mi moderu: Anakonda

fruit.name: Fruit of the Reptile, Cobra Royal version
fruit.description: allows the user to transform himself into a cobra as he pleases: he can cast deadly poison, can transform his hair into a snake and is impervious to fire.
fruit.roman_name: Hebi Hebi no Mi moderu: Kingu Kobura

crew.name: The crew of the Lion d'Or

fruit.name: Floating Fruit
fruit.description: It enables its user to lift objects by controlling gravity. Since its user has swords for legs, he can also fly. (Although this fruit appeared in a movie, its use was demonstrated in chapter 0 of One Piece explaining Shiki's escape from Impel Down prison).

crew.name: The crew of the Lion d'Or

fruit.name: Fruit du Marais
fruit.description: the body of the eater turns to mud and becomes a living swamp. He can create bottomless swamps to prevent his victims from escaping: the more his victims struggle, the deeper they sink. Thanks to this principle, he can enclose them in his body while retaining his original size. It also allows him to keep weapons inside his body, such as a machine gun or a scythe, and to draw them out for use when needed.

fruit.name: Fruit of Souls
fruit.description: Allows you to manipulate the souls of human beings as you wish. The user can introduce a soul into an object or animal to bring it to life and humanize it, i.e. give it consciousness and the gift of speech. These beings are called 'Homies'. The user can also divide his or her own soul into fragments that live on as avatars of the fruit eater. The main role of these avatars is to harvest fragments of life from living beings and redistribute them to their owners. People with no fear of death or psychic powers are more resistant to this fruit.

fruit.name: Glutinous Rice Fruit
fruit.description: Allows the user to generate glutinous rice at will. This allows the user to block anyone's attacks and trap them in a large quantity of glutinous rice. What's more, it has several similarities with the Gum Gum fruit, such as elongating limbs and blocking all gunfire. However, the substance dissolves after receiving a large quantity of water. It's a special Paramecia.

fruit.name: Horse Fruit
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-horse. Since its user is a bird, this has turned him into a half-bird, half-horse creature. This transforms him into a kind of pegasus.

fruit.name: Cookie Fruit
fruit.description: Allows the user to produce and manipulate cookies at will. The user can cover himself in cookies to create an alter-ego different from himself, and create a multitude of copies of the same alter-ego. Cookies can be rendered ineffective by the use of water, making them easier for enemies to eat.

fruit.name: Fruit de la Léchouille
fruit.description: Allows the user to turn objects into sweets and then lick them off. It can also turn living creatures into sweets, killing them in the process. In addition, the user can create complex objects such as escalators with the same functions as their 'real' versions. On the other hand, sweets can melt after a certain period of time due to heat or fire, and can also be eaten.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Lamp
fruit.description: Enables the user to summon a powerful genie from his body and attack opponents with it. This genie is armed with a halberd.

fruit.name: Fruit of Heat
fruit.description: Allows the user to heat body parts and transfer heat to objects. The heat generated by the user makes him/her more resistant to edged weapons.

fruit.name: Fruit de la Crème
fruit.description: Allows the user to produce and manipulate cream at will.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Mirror
fruit.description: Allows the user to repeat the gestures of opponents and reflect their attacks. It is also possible to reflect people onto animals. Living beings can be captured in the mirrors and find themselves in a world where the mirrors are merely access points to that world. These mirrors are sources of information for the user and others currently in the mirror world, following questions that may be asked by them (e.g., communicating a person's position, etc.).

fruit.name: Fruit of the Book
fruit.description: Allows the user to manipulate books at will, creating dimensions within the book's pages to trap objects or living beings. However, burning the books will free those trapped inside.

fruit.name: Butter Fruit
fruit.description: Allows the user to produce and manipulate butter at will.

fruit.name: Fruit of Memories
fruit.description: Allows the user to extract a person's memory in film format. In this way, he can manipulate the person's memory by subtracting unwanted memories and/or inserting memories previously taken from other victims. When certain people become amnesiac, the user can make them temporarily recover their memories.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Mix
fruit.description: Allows the user to merge with other people.

fruit.name: Turtle Fruit
fruit.description: whoever eats it can transform into a turtle with an indestructible shell. As strong as diamond, it protects its user from firearms and collapsing buildings, among other hazards.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Egg
fruit.description: allows the user to transform his body composition into an egg. Each time it is seriously injured, the user regenerates into a more and more accomplished form of chicken, exponentially increasing its physical capacities.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Cook
fruit.description: Allows the user to transform natural objects into ingredients for subsequent consumption.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Fish, Azure Dragon version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can transform into an azure dragon.
fruit.roman_name: Uo Uo no Mi, Moderu Seiryū

fruit.name: Fruit of the Dinosaur, Pteranodon version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a pteranodon.
fruit.roman_name: Ryū Ryū no Mi Kodai-shu Moderu Puteranodon

fruit.name: Fruit of the Dinosaur, Brachiosaurus version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a brachiosaurus.
fruit.roman_name: Ryū Ryū no Mi Moderu Burakiosaurusu

fruit.name: Fruit of the Pachyderm, Mammoth version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a mammoth. It increases the strength and length of its owner in an exceptional way. The hardness of its skin also gives it a certain resistance to physical attack.
fruit.roman_name: Zō Zō no Mi, moderu Manmosu

fruit.name: Fruit of the Dinosaur, Spinosaurus version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a spinosaurus.
fruit.roman_name: Ryū Ryū no Mi Moderu Supinosaurusu

fruit.name: Fruit of the Dinosaur, Pachycephalosaurus version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a pachycephalosaurus.
fruit.roman_name: Ryū Ryū no Mi Moderu Pakikefarosaurusu

fruit.name: Fruit du Félin, saber-toothed tiger version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a phoenix. It can regenerate and heal the wounds of other living beings.
fruit.roman_name: Tori Tori no Mi, Moderu Fenikkusu

fruit.name: Spider fruit, Rosamygale grauvogeli version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a rosamygale grauvogeli.
fruit.roman_name: Kumo Kumo no Mi Moderu Rosamigare Guraubogerī

fruit.name: Fruit of the Dinosaur, Triceratops version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a triceratops.
fruit.roman_name: Ryū Ryū no Mi Moderu Torikeratopusu

fruit.description: transforms into a pug

fruit.name: Fruit of the Sound
fruit.description: Enables the user to transform body parts into instruments and use them as weapons.

fruit.name: Fruit of Darkness
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into darkness. It becomes capable of altering gravity so as to attract and absorb just about anything in a 'black hole' and then release it. It can also cancel the powers of other demon fruit users when it touches them. Moreover, it is the only Logia that cannot avoid physical blows, so its user becomes highly sensitive to pain. It can also absorb the power of its owner's demon fruit, as Marshall D. Teach will do with Whitebeard.

fruit.name: Fruit of strength
fruit.description: It's a fruit that allows the eater to acquire Herculean strength.

fruit.name: Fruit of Invisibility
fruit.description: Enables the user to make himself and everything he touches (living beings, firearms, etc.) invisible.

fruit.name: Fruit of teleportation
fruit.description: It's a demon fruit that allows the eater to teleport himself and anything else from one place to another.

fruit.name: Island fruit
fruit.description: It's a demon fruit that allows its user to become one with an entire island, thus becoming an Island Man.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Canidae, Nine-tailed Fox version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a nine-tailed fox.
fruit.roman_name: Inu Inu no Mi, Moderu Kyūbi no Kitsune

fruit.name: The fruit of gigantism
fruit.description: It's a demon fruit that allows its user to increase his size, making him a Gigantified Man.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Gobbledygook
fruit.description: It's a demon fruit that allows its user to control alcohol, making him a Man-Alcohol.

fruit.name: Fruit of the disease
fruit.description: It's a demon fruit that allows the eater to create any form of contagious, virulent disease.

fruit.name: Fruit of Trembling
fruit.description: Enables the user to create seismic waves, causing earthquakes or cracks (even in the surrounding air) that destroy anything within their zone of effect. The strength of these waves varies according to the user's desire, and they can be disproportionately large. The power of this fruit is so great that it can also cause tsunamis or abysses. Seismic waves can cover weapons to increase the power of their blows tenfold.

fruit.name: Pyro-Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into fire. It can therefore create powerful explosions and control ambient temperatures. It can also use its fire to propel itself and move much faster. However, fire is no match for magma.

fruit.name: Sparkling Fruit
fruit.description: Enables the user to transform his body into a diamond. It then possesses extraordinary resistance.

fruit.name: Fruit de la Poche
fruit.description: Allows the user to create pockets on their body to store objects.

crew.name: Faux Equipage du Chapeau de Paille
Faux Equipage du Chapeau de Paille
Faux Equipage du Chapeau de Paille
Faux Equipage du Chapeau de Paille
Faux Equipage du Chapeau de Paille

Faux Equipage du Chapeau de Paille

fruit.name: Fruit du Fil
fruit.description: Allows you to take control of someone and use them as a puppet, as well as to easily cut people and objects of various sizes in a large area. It also enables its user to cling to clouds to 'fly', to link several wires together to create a sharp whip, and in a 'combined' version in ball form to 'fire' wire bullets like a pistol shot. And last but not least, he can create a clone from strings that has the same abilities as its owner, and this clone is impervious to bladed weapons. Thanks to his fruit, the user can administer first aid by stitching up organs and open wounds.

fruit.name: Poisse-Poisse fruit
fruit.description: the eater's body can generate mucus at will. This mucus has the following characteristics: sticky, adherent and flammable. It can therefore be used to grip objects, stick to any surface or ignite it.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Wind Thief
fruit.description: Transforms the hard consistency of an object such as a steel cape into that of a flag. Its user can even make a sword 'soft' and then re-solidify it once it has taken on a different shape. It can also become a floating flag in its own right.

fruit.name: Fruit de la Caillasse
fruit.description: Allows its holder to melt into stone and create any shape he wishes as an exponentially larger clone of himself. It can alter and control the shape of any rock object or structure at will.

fruit.name: Fruit du Joujou
fruit.description: Transforms any person into a toy by simply touching them. Transformed people no longer have control over their bodies and obey orders given to them (at least, if the user has given them any). The effects of this fruit stop the growth of its user the moment he eats it. People turned into toys are forgotten, all memories of them disappear and they are preserved from aging. If the user falls unconscious, all the people become themselves again, and the memories of those who had forgotten them resurface.

fruit.name: Fruit of Art
fruit.description: Enables the user to create a mist that transforms everything it touches into a work of art. Any being or object transformed into a work of art loses its original functionality.

name: Lao G
job: Lieutenant of the Army of Diamante

name: Señor Pink

fruit.name: Fruit of the Barbotage
fruit.description: Allows the user to liquefy any surface around him. This means he can swim through surfaces such as walls or even the floor.

job: Lieutenant of the Army of Diamante

name: Machvise

fruit.name: Fruit of the Tonne-Tonne
fruit.description: Its user can float in the air and then land on the enemy to crush him to the ground, very quickly.

job: Lieutenant of the Army of Diamante

name: Dellinger
job: Lieutenant of the Army of Diamante

fruit.name: Fruit of the Paf-Paf
fruit.description: Inflates an object to the point of rupture, causing it to explode and the user to explode on contact.

fruit.name: Fruit of the whirlwind
fruit.description: Allows the user to make every part of his body rotate, enabling him to fly through the air and produce hurricanes by rotating a specific part of his body at full speed.

fruit.name: Fruit du Flocon
fruit.description: the body of the eater turns to snow. It can create a violent blizzard, solid snow barriers or even igloos. He can also use his body to chill opponents, putting them in a state of stasis, for example. He can also transform himself into a snow "monster", endowing himself with a pair of snow wings and transforming these parts into ice as sharp and solid as steel. It can also shape snow creatures (e.g. snow rabbits) and use them as projectiles. Finally, the user can use his power to manipulate snow spikes as sabers.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Pachyderm
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-elephant. Given that its user is a sword, this has turned it into a half-sword, half-elephant being. Having acquired consciousness and thus a certain intelligence, it can have phenomenal reach.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Pachyderm
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-elephant. Given that its user is a sword, this has turned it into a half-sword, half-elephant being. Having acquired consciousness and thus a certain intelligence, it can have phenomenal reach.

fruit.name: Fruit du Bovin, Giraffe version
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half giraffe. His kicks and nose strikes are much more powerful (especially with the Rokushiki Shigan).
fruit.roman_name: Ushi Ushi no Mi moderu Kirin

fruit.name: Poison Fruit
fruit.description: Allows its user to secrete a panoply of poisons and toxic gases. The effects of these venoms change according to the user's needs. Users can shape their creations in any way they like, and can even cover their entire body with poison to protect themselves.

fruit.name: Magma Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into lava. It can then melt anything and almost anyone. It can also create giant lava hands which, after being launched into the atmosphere, bring volcanic particles down to earth, causing great damage. Fire is powerless against magma.

fruit.name: Luminescent Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into light. He can then move and strike almost anyone quickly. It can also move at the speed of light, emit explosive rays of light, blind enemies and create weapons made of light (swords, spears, etc.).

fruit.name: Fruit of Gravity
fruit.description: Allows the user to manipulate gravity around a specific location by sending gravitational forces such as boulders, meteorites or exerting force against an opponent on the ground.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Laundry
fruit.description: Enables its user to cleanse people of their impure hearts and lay them on a thread. These people can then no longer move.

fruit.name: Fruit Smoke
fruit.description: the eater's body turns to smoke. He can then create smoke to catch his opponents, and can propel himself with his smoke to move faster and fly.

fruit.name: Fruit du Séquestre
fruit.description: Enables the user to imprison opponents by coming into contact with them. These constrictive bonds are made of a rapidly hardening substance.

fruit.name: Berry Fruit
fruit.description: Enables its user to divide his body into berry-like parts and thus bounce off any surface. It is therefore immune to punches and blunt weapons.

fruit.name: Rust fruit
fruit.description: Enables its owner to rust anything he touches. It can therefore rust any bladed weapon or living creature's limbs.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Wheels
fruit.description: Allows its owner to transform body parts into wheels and spin them at high speed.

fruit.name: Sourdine fruit
fruit.description: Create sound-absorbing barriers to totally cancel out the sounds produced by the system (or from an area in which it is located) and those coming from outside.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Human, Buddha version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can transform into an imposing Daibutsu, considerably increasing his physical strength. It can generate shockwaves.
fruit.roman_name: Hito Hito no Mi moderu Daibutsu

fruit.name: Fruit of the Dinosaur, Allosaurus version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into an allosaurus.
fruit.roman_name: Ryū Ryū no Mi Moderu Arosaurusu

name: Woop Slap
job: Mayor of the village of Fuchsia

name: Boodle
job: Mayor of the village of Orange

fruit.name: Fruit of the Glutton
fruit.description: Allows its user to eat anything and integrate this food into his own body. For example, if he eats a cannon, his tongue can transform into a real cannon. It can also fuse together the beings it has eaten, and self-ingest to slim down.

name: Chaka

fruit.name: Fruit of the Canidae, Jackal version
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half jackal. Its agility in hybrid form is far superior to the average.
fruit.roman_name: Inu Inu no Mi moderu Jakkaru

fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half hawk. This power gives him keen eyesight, surprising speed and the ability to fly.

name: Tilestone
job: Galley-La Company (head of cabinetmakers, sailmakers and sailmakers)

fruit.name: Fruit of Time
fruit.description: Allows the user to travel into the future.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Garment
fruit.description: Enables its user to create garments from leaves or stones.

fruit.name: Fruit of Maturation
fruit.description: Enables the user to ripen and decompose inanimate objects. It can also age living beings.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Reptile, eight-headed dragon version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into an eight-headed dragon.
fruit.roman_name: Hebi Hebi no Mi moderu Yamata no Orochi

fruit.name: Fruit of the Brush
fruit.description: Allows users to generate ink from their bodies and transform the drawings created with this ink into realistic, three-dimensional objects.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Barrier
fruit.description: Enables its user to generate almost invisible barriers to deflect or block any attack. These barriers can take on a wide range of shapes (racket, stairs, etc.).

fruit.name: Travesti-Fruit
fruit.description: Allows you to change your appearance by touching your face with your right hand, and to return to your normal appearance by touching your face with your left hand. You only need to touch a person once for their appearance to be remembered forever. The user can also assemble parts of different people, but is unable to attack unless he possesses his own face and body.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Human, Onyudo version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into an Onyudo
fruit.roman_name: Hito Hito no Mi, Moderu: Ōnyūdō

fruit.name: Millet fruit
fruit.description: Allows the user to generate dangos and then render servile any animal that consumes them. This works on SMILES users, but not on Zoan demon fruit users.

fruit.name: Canid Fruit, Tanuki version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can transform into a tanuki.
fruit.roman_name: Inu Inu no Mi Moderu Bake-danuki

fruit.name: Fruit of the Canid, Divine Wolf version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into a divine wolf.
fruit.roman_name: Inu Inu no Mi Moderu Ōkuchi no Makami

fruit.name: Fruit of the Salamander, Axolotl version
fruit.description: Those who eat it can transform into an axolotl, the user being an enormous living gelatinous mass made of a flammable product, it can move much faster to charge its victims and subdivide into a multitude of smaller creatures like the original version.
fruit.roman_name: Sara Sara no Mi moderu: Ahorōtoru

fruit.name: Fruit of the Eye
fruit.description: Enables its user to read people's minds, transmit his own memories to someone else, and generate tears of various shapes (e.g. whale-shaped tears with enough power to pulverize wooden crates and stun a group of people). It also enables its user to observe events taking place far away, by "transmuting" his gaze into a bird's-eye view of everything happening within a given perimeter.

fruit.name: Fruit of Healing
fruit.description: Temporarily heals any living thing through the user's tears. It can permanently heal the wounded by taking a little vital energy from healthy people (this energy takes the form of a dandelion flower). By extension, its user can repair any object, but at the expense of its life expectancy.

fruit.name: Fruit de la Pelisse
fruit.description: Allows the user to appropriate the physical and mental capacities of a living being (human or animal) by wearing it in the same way as a jacket.

fruit.name: Phoenix Fruit
fruit.description: It transforms into a Phoenix or a hybrid form

fruit.name: Horse Fruit
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-horse. Since its user is a bird, this has turned him into a half-bird, half-horse creature. This transforms him into a kind of pegasus.

job: Skypiea (exiled) / Clan Ener (Prelate of the Balloon Ordinary)

job: Skypiea (exiled) / Clan Ener (Prelate of the ordination of sons)

job: Skypiea (exile) / Clan Ener (captain of the sacred guard)

name: Hotori
job: Skypiea (exiled) / Clan Ener (vice captain of the sacred guard)

name: Kotori
job: Skypiea (exiled) / Clan Ener (vice captain of the sacred guard)

fruit.name: Fulguro-Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into lightning. It can therefore move at lightning speed and strike anything except non-conductive elements such as rubber. He can create powerful thunderstorms or spheres of lightning. By combining Haki with its lightning, its user can hear things from over 1 kilometer away. He can also revive himself if he falls unconscious.

fruit.name: Pyro-Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into fire. It can therefore create powerful explosions and control ambient temperatures. It can also use its fire to propel itself and move much faster. However, fire is no match for magma.

fruit.name: Fruit of Hormones
fruit.description: Allows its user to secrete hormones and inject them into himself or someone else. These hormones can modify the body of the person to whom they are injected: for example, their sex can be changed. They can also heal, revitalize (adrenalin) or enlarge a body part.

fruit.name: Fruit of Exaltation
fruit.description: Allows the user to motivate people in a fight and awaken their latent power to fight.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Pousse-Pousse
fruit.description: Allows the user to manipulate and move through rock like clay. It can also be used to create tunnels.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Scissors
fruit.description: Allows users to transform their hands into scissors that cut absolutely anything, from sheets of paper to brick walls. Any cut material can be handled with ease.

fruit.name: Sea Urchin Fruit
fruit.description: Allows you to transform any part of your body (even your hair) into spikes strong enough to pierce stone walls. These spikes can also be used to perform acupuncture techniques to increase the user's own muscle mass.

fruit.name: Travesti-Fruit
fruit.description: Allows you to change your appearance by touching your face with your right hand, and to return to your normal appearance by touching your face with your left hand. You only need to touch a person once for their appearance to be remembered forever. The user can also assemble parts of different people, but is unable to attack unless he possesses his own face and body.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Canid, Basset version
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half basset hound. Given that its user is a firearm, this has turned it into a half-gun, half-dog creature.
fruit.roman_name: Inu Inu no Mi moderu Dakkusufunto

fruit.name: Digging Fruit
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-mole. It can dig gigantic galleries in almost any material.

fruit.name: Fruit Boum-Boum
fruit.description: The user can make any part of his body explode, including his boogers and breath, rendering him insensitive to explosions. The user can combine his power with a pistol, which he reloads by blowing into it.

fruit.name: Kilo-Kilo Fruit
fruit.description: Allows the user's mass to be varied between a featherweight and 10 tons. Note that the user's volume does not change when he changes his mass.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Canid, Wolf version
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes half-wolf. Its strength and speed are greater in hybrid form.
fruit.roman_name: Inu Inu no Mi moderu: Ōkami

fruit.name: Fruit of the Porter
fruit.description: Allows the user to transform anything he touches into a door: a wall, part of a human body or a vacuum. In the latter case, the user 'disappears' into another dimension and can go anywhere by opening a door at a specific point.

fruit.name: Fruit des Bulles
fruit.description: Allows its possessor to produce soap bubbles that clean everything to the point of removing the force itself. It also soaps the skin, making enemies so slippery they can barely move or hold anything in their hands.

fruit.name: Frost Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into ice. It can freeze anything and almost anyone, launching super-powerful waves of icy air that can freeze everything in their path, and is immune to temperature differentials when it intensifies the ambient cold. Its user can neutralize opponents in a flash, or even freeze a vast expanse of water for 1 week.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Spring
fruit.description: Transform parts of your body into springs that bounce back at impressive speed, increasing the power of your blows.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Pads
fruit.description: Thanks to the pads held in the hands, the user can project powerful shockwaves, teleport or repel anything and everything, including pain and physical attacks. The user can 'dispatch' opponents anywhere.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Gas
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into gas. As a result, his body can change shape at will. It can float high above the ground and slip through any narrow or otherwise inaccessible passage. It seems to be immune to certain poisons, can create others such as hallucinogenic gases and can even purify intoxicated air. He can suffocate his victims by depriving them of oxygen. It can also create an explosive gas and spit a beam capable of melting metal.

fruit.name: Fruit du Volatile, Albatross version
fruit.description: whoever eats it can turn into an albatross.
fruit.roman_name: Tori Tori no Mi Moderu Arubatorosu

fruit.name: Fruit of the Vocalise
fruit.description: the person who has eaten this fruit uses sound beams converted into lasers to destroy everything in his path.

fruit.name: Unbreakable Fruit
fruit.description: whoever eats it becomes as hard as rock, and can increase the heat of certain body parts so that his opponent burns himself by touching them.

fruit.name: Fruit of Dissolution
fruit.description: This fruit enables its user to dissolve anything into liquid, including himself, by shooting rays into his opponents' eyes.

fruit.name: Candy Fruit
fruit.description: the body of the eater is transformed into syrup. It can also contain any solid mass passing through it (swords, fists, feet, etc.). However, it is vulnerable if hit by a mealy substance.

fruit.name: Chamquipue fruit
fruit.description: the person eating the fruit can create poisonous spores. These spores can take various forms (laser beams, clones, etc.). Of course, the user is immune to poison, but his power is vulnerable to fire.

crew.name: The crew of the Lion d'Or
The crew of the Lion d'Or
The crew of the Lion d'Or

fruit.name: Fruit of the Volatile, Eagle version
fruit.description: Very similar to the Falcon version of Fruit du Volatile
fruit.roman_name: Tori Tori no Mi moderu Washi

fruit.name: Fruit Jeune-Jeune
fruit.description: This fruit allows its holder to rejuvenate people and return objects to their state 12 years ago (for example, volcanic rocks will return to their lava state). This power is manifested by the creation of a pink aura with which the user must touch the target to activate it. The more the object or person is touched by this power, the younger it becomes. If the number of touches exceeds the age of the person or object touched (minus 12 years for each touch), he/she disappears permanently.

fruit.name: Fluffy Fruit
fruit.description: This fruit enables its user to accelerate the growth rate of plants and control them at will. Its user can use it mainly to trap or attack enemies with vines, but also to protect himself from enemy attacks. However, it can only grow plants in environments where vegetation is present.

fruit.name: Fruit of Gold
fruit.description: This fruit allows its user to manipulate gold at will. He can transform solid objects into gold and melt them as well. He can coat his body in gold, transforming himself into a giant solid gold golem. He can also make buildings out of gold and control them.

fruit.name: Fruit of Luck
fruit.description: This fruit enables its user to steal luck from those he touches and use it for himself.

fruit.name: Passe-Muraille fruit
fruit.description: This fruit allows its user to pass through solid objects to escape or pass through walls.

fruit.name: Fruit de la Ferraille
fruit.description: This fruit enables its user to manipulate and combine objects such as iron and weapons.

fruit.name: Fruit of Vision
fruit.description: This fruit enables him to create temporary illusions in the shape of the desired person.

fruit.name: Chamquipue fruit
fruit.description: the person eating the fruit can create poisonous spores. These spores can take various forms (laser beams, clones, etc.). Of course, the user is immune to poison, but his power is vulnerable to fire.

fruit.name: Fruit du Ciboulot
fruit.description: Nomi Nomi no Mi is a Paramecia-type Demon Fruit that allows the brain of its eater to grow indefinitely as it ingests new knowledge, transforming the eater into a Brain-Man.

fruit.name: Horse fruit, Pegasus model
fruit.description: This demon fruit allows the user to transform into a flying winged horse or a hybrid flying winged horse.
fruit.roman_name: Uma Uma no Mi, modèle Pégase

fruit.name: Passion fruit
fruit.description: Allows its possessor to use love as a lethal weapon through a variety of means. These techniques are designed to petrify people or objects, and are all heart-shaped (rays, piercing kisses, kicks, etc.). This power only works on people with an attraction (however slight) for the user. When the user reverses the process, the victim has no memory of the time spent petrified.

fruit.name: Slashing Fruit
fruit.description: Allows you to transform parts of your body into sharp steel. Its owner can, for example, transform his body into sharp blades to protect him, or his arms into sharp blades.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Pads
fruit.description: Thanks to the pads held in the hands, the user can project powerful shockwaves, teleport or repel anything and everything, including pain and physical attacks. The user can 'dispatch' opponents anywhere.

fruit.name: Fruit of the Barbotage
fruit.description: Allows the user to liquefy any surface around him. This means he can swim through surfaces such as walls or even the floor.
